# 🏛 **Africana Studies - Angela Davis**

> _“I am no longer accepting the things I cannot change. I am changing the things I cannot accept.”_ — Angela Davis

---

## 📌 **Overview**

**Angela Davis** (b. January 26, 1944) is a revolutionary **activist, scholar, author, and former political prisoner** who has dedicated her life to **fighting systemic oppression, mass incarceration, and racial and gender justice**. A key figure in the **Black Power Movement, feminist thought, and prison abolition**, Davis was associated with the **Black Panther Party, the Communist Party USA, and the Soledad Brothers Defense Committee**.

Her intellectual contributions to **critical race theory, intersectionality, and Black feminism** continue to influence movements for racial and social justice worldwide.

