## 📜 **Timeline**

📍 **1944** – Born in Birmingham, Alabama, in a neighborhood nicknamed _Dynamite Hill_ due to frequent KKK bombings.  
📍 **1963** – Witnesses the **16th Street Baptist Church bombing**, which kills four Black girls, shaping her activism.  
📍 **1969** – Joins the faculty at **UCLA**, but is fired due to her Communist Party affiliation.  
📍 **1970-72** – Arrested and imprisoned for her alleged involvement in a courtroom shootout. She becomes a **global political prisoner**, sparking the _Free Angela Davis_ movement.  
📍 **1980s-90s** – Publishes works on **feminism, race, class, and prison abolition**.  
📍 **2000s-Present** – Continues her activism, focusing on **mass incarceration, abolitionism, and intersectionality**.

